fields.name: Tent pitch
fields.description: Grass pitch. No electric hook up. Size 8m x 6m.

fields.name: Caravan or Campervan pitch
fields.description: Grass or hard-standing pitches available. Size 12m x 10m. Electric hookup included.

fields.name: Glamping tent
fields.description: A stunning glamping dome that is fully equipped for everything you need to enjoy a night of luxury under canvas. Includes a super comfy double-bed, sofa, kitchen area, lighting and electricity.

fields.name: BBQ
fields.description: A portable, charcoal bbq perfect for grilling your own food during your stay. Large cooking surface suitable for up to 6 people. Comes with 3 utensils (tongs, fork and spatula).

fields.name: Dog
fields.description: One friendly, well-behaved dog. Please keep your dog on a lead and clean up behing your dog.

fields.name: Segway
fields.description: Jump on board one of our all-terrain Segways for a fast and fun way to explore the forest trails.

fields.name: Mountain biking
fields.description: What better way to explore the forest than at your own pace on two-wheels? With 5 superb bike trails ranging from our 10km Rookie trail to the 40km Black trail, this activity is great fun whether a novice or experienced rider. Hire a bike and give it a go today.

fields.name: Guided walking
fields.description: Enjoy a 10 mile guided walking along the River and Railway path. Discover the mining history, learn about the flora and fauna and enjoy a mix of trail, woodland and gravel tracks. Suitable for all abilities.

fields.name: Guided hiking
fields.description: Explore some of the finest mountains in South Wales with this tough but rewarding 25 mile guided hike along the Gyfylchi Ridgetop Trial. With steep ascents and descents and some technical sections, this hike is for people with a good level of fitness and with previous hiking experience. A tough day out but the views from the ridge above the forest are the ultimate reward.
